segments.title: AI Introduction and Overview
segments.summary: Introduces the main topics of artificial intelligence, machine learning, and deep learning. Discusses how these technologies relate to each other and addresses common misconceptions.

segments.title: Early AI History
segments.summary: Describes the early days of AI starting from its research origins. Mentions early programming languages like LISP and Prolog, and the development of expert systems in the 1980s.

segments.title: Deep Learning Neural Networks
segments.summary: Explains deep learning and neural networks as a way to simulate human brain function. Discusses how these networks can be unpredictable and difficult to fully understand due to their multiple layers.

segments.title: Generative AI Explanation
segments.summary: Introduces generative AI and foundation models, including large language models. Explains how these technologies can generate new content and predict language patterns.

segments.title: AI Adoption Timeline
segments.summary: Describes how AI adoption evolved from slow beginnings to rapid acceleration with the introduction of foundation models and generative AI.
